! Static (Declarative) Clusters

For hardcoded grouping without drag-drop, set `cluster` directly on `<$node>`. Container nodes use the `__cluster__` prefix.

<div style="height:450px;border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:4px;margin:8px 0;">
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="__cluster__Engineering" label="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:frontend" label="Frontend" cluster="__cluster__Engineering" color="RoyalBlue"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:backend" label="Backend" cluster="__cluster__Engineering" color="RoyalBlue"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:devops" label="DevOps" cluster="__cluster__Engineering" color="RoyalBlue"/>

  <$node $tiddler="__cluster__Sales" label="Sales"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:retail" label="Retail" cluster="__cluster__Sales" color="DarkOrange"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:enterprise" label="Enterprise" cluster="__cluster__Sales" color="DarkOrange"/>

  <$edge $from="sc:frontend" $to="sc:backend"/>
  <$edge $from="sc:backend" $to="sc:devops"/>
  <$edge $from="sc:frontend" $to="sc:retail" stroke="dashed"/>
</$graph>
</div>

!! Source

```
<div style="height:450px;border:1px solid #ddd;border-radius:4px;margin:8px 0;">
<$graph>
  <$node $tiddler="__cluster__Engineering" label="Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:frontend" label="Frontend" cluster="__cluster__Engineering"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:backend" label="Backend" cluster="__cluster__Engineering"/>

  <$node $tiddler="__cluster__Sales" label="Sales"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:retail" label="Retail" cluster="__cluster__Sales"/>
  <$node $tiddler="sc:enterprise" label="Enterprise" cluster="__cluster__Sales"/>

  <$edge $from="sc:frontend" $to="sc:backend"/>
  <$edge $from="sc:frontend" $to="sc:retail" stroke="dashed"/>
</$graph>
</div>
```

Note: The `__cluster__` prefix tells the Cytoscape adapter to style the node as a compound container (dashed border, semi-transparent background, label at top).
